CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 15, 1941, pg. 12, reads: "To Be Guests At Football Jamboree - When the annual Football Jamboree is held Friday night, Nov. 14 at the St. Moritz ballroom, the above beauties will represent their high schools and bring their delegation of friends to make this the largest and most successful Jamboree to date. The back row, left to right, shows Arleen Mills of Westinghouse; Alverta Thomas, of Washington (Pa.) high; and June Hamilton of Peabody.  The front row presents: Helen Robinson, South Hills; Ella Mae Lacey, Washington (Pa.) high; Frances Moore, Schenley; and Vivian Shephard, Fifth Avenue high."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, back row from left: Helen Robinson, Alverta Thomas, Frances Moore, Ella Mae Lacey, Vivian Shephard; front row: June Hamilton and Arleen Mills posed with footballs for annual Football Jamboree, in Harris Studio
